   "cell_type": "code",

   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1500x1000 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, axs = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(15, 10), sharex=\"col\")\n",
    "\n",
    "colors = {\n",
    "    \"numu\": \"darkgreen\",\n",
    "    \"antinumu\": \"darkseagreen\",\n",
    "    \"nue\": \"red\",\n",
    "    \"antinue\": \"rosybrown\",\n",
    "    \"nutau\": \"teal\",\n",
    "    \"antinutau\": \"cadetblue\",\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "for key in [\"numu\", \"nue\", \"antinumu\", \"antinue\"]:\n",
    "    for i in [0, 1]:\n",
    "        axs[0, i].step(\n",
    "            t2kflux_2020_plus250kA_nominal_sk.minE,\n",
    "            t2kflux_2020_plus250kA_nominal_sk[key],\n",
    "            label=conv.print_dict[key],\n",
    "            color=colors[key],\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        axs[1, i].step(\n",
    "            t2kflux_2020_plus250kA_nominal_sk.minE,\n",
    "            t2kflux_2020_plus250kA_nominal_sk[\"true\" + key],\n",
    "            label=conv.print_dict[key],\n",
    "            color=colors[key],\n",
    "        )\n",
    "\n",
    "for ax in axs.reshape(-1):\n",
    "    ax.set_xscale(\"log\")\n",
    "    ax.legend()\n",
    "    ax.text(\n",
    "        x=0.6,\n",
    "        y=0.5,\n",
    "        s=r\"600 MeV\",\n",
    "        ha=\"right\",\n",
    "        va=\"top\",\n",
    "        rotation=90,\n",
    "        transform=ax.get_xaxis_transform(),\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    ax.axvline(x=0.6, linestyle=\"--\", color=\"black\")\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in [0, 1]:\n",
    "    axs[i, 0].set_yscale(\"log\")\n",
    "    # axs[i,0].set_ylim(bottom=1e-1)\n",
    "    axs[i, 1].yaxis.tick_right()\n",
    "    axs[1, i].set_xlabel(r\"$E$ [GeV]\")\n",
    "\n",
    "axs[0, 0].set_ylabel(\n",
    "    r\"Flux [$\\text{cm}^{-2}\\cdot (50\\,\\text{MeV})^{-1} \\cdot (10^{21}\\,\\text{PoT})^{-1}$]\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "axs[1, 0].set_ylabel(r\"Flux integrated per bin [$\\text{PoT}^{-1}$]\")\n",

   "source": [
    "summed_integral = t2kflux_2020_plus250kA_nominal_sk.truetotal.sum()\n",
    "integrals = {\n",
    "    key: [t2kflux_2020_plus250kA_nominal_sk[\"true\" + key].sum()]\n",
    "    for key in [\"numu\", \"nue\", \"antinumu\", \"antinue\"]\n",
    "}\n",
    "for key in [\"numu\", \"nue\", \"antinumu\", \"antinue\"]:\n",
    "    integrals[key].append(integrals[key][0] / summed_integral)\n",
    "pd.DataFrame(integrals, index=[\"abs\", \"relat\"])"
   ]
  },

    "<p> </p>"
   ]

   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "So that the integrated flux at SK (2020, nominal, FHC) per chanel is\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\begin{matrix}\n",
    "    \\Phi_{\\nu_\\mu} & = & 12.073 & 10^{-15}\\ \\text{cm}^{-2} \\cdot \\text{PoT}^{-1} & & & (92.51 \\%) \\\\\n",
    "    \\Phi_{\\nu_e} & = & 0.143 & 10^{-15}\\ \\text{cm}^{-2} \\cdot \\text{PoT}^{-1} & & & (1.10 \\%) \\\\\n",
    "    \\Phi_{\\overline{\\nu}_\\mu} & = & 0.812 & 10^{-15}\\ \\text{cm}^{-2} \\cdot \\text{PoT}^{-1} & & & (6.22 \\%) \\\\\n",
    "    \\Phi_{\\overline{\\nu}_e} & = & 0.022 & 10^{-15}\\ \\text{cm}^{-2} \\cdot \\text{PoT}^{-1} & & & (0.17 \\%) \\\\ \\\\\n",
    "    \\hline \\\\\n",
    "    \\Phi_\\text{tot} & = & 13.051 & (10^{-15}\\ \\text{cm}^{-2} \\cdot \\text{PoT})^{-1} & & & (100 \\%) \n",
    "\\end{matrix}\n",
    "$$"
   ]

    "<p> </p>\n",
    "The data is not very smooth, since it has been read-out from a figure in an article. We can use the Savitzky-Golay filter to smooth it a little."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {
    "metadata": {}
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ccqe_filtered = conv.xsecimport(name=\"neutrino_ccqe.csv\", mode=\"true filter\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {
    "metadata": {}
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x500 with 3 Axes>"
      ]

     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.step(ccqe_true.energy, ccqe_true.xsec, label=r\"CCQE (raw)\", where=\"mid\")\n",
    "plt.step(\n",
    "    ccqe_filtered.energy, ccqe_filtered.xsec, label=r\"CCQE (filtered)\", where=\"mid\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "plt.axvline(x=0.6, linestyle=\"--\", color=\"black\")\n",
    "ax = plt.gca()\n",
    "plt.text(\n",
    "    x=0.6,\n",
    "    y=0.5,\n",
    "    s=r\"600 MeV\",\n",
    "    ha=\"right\",\n",
    "    va=\"top\",\n",

    "    transform=ax.get_xaxis_transform(),\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xscale(\"log\")\n",
    "# plt.yscale(\"log\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(r\"$E$ [GeV]\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(r\"$\\nu$ cross-section [$\\text{cm}^2$]\")\n",
    "# plt.ylim(bottom=0)\n",
    "plt.title(\n",
    "    r\"CCQE neutrino cross-section per nucleon, filtered with a Savitzky-Golay filter\"\n",

    "for xlim, ylim, loc in [\n",

    "    ((0.08, 0.12), (-0.1e-39, 0.1e-39), (8, 2, 4)),\n",
    "]:\n",
    "    axins = inloc.inset_axes(ax, width=\"17%\", height=\"35%\", loc=loc[0], borderpad=3)\n",
    "    axins.set_xlim(*xlim)\n",
    "    axins.set_ylim(*ylim)\n",
    "    plt.step(ccqe_true.energy, ccqe_true.xsec, where=\"mid\")\n",
    "    plt.step(ccqe_filtered.energy, ccqe_filtered.xsec, where=\"mid\")\n",
    "    axins.grid(True, \"both\")\n",
    "    inloc.mark_inset(ax, axins, loc1=loc[1], loc2=loc[2], fc=\"none\", ec=\"0.5\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},

   "cell_type": "code",

    "for xlim, ylim, loc in [\n",

    "    axins.set_ylim(*ylim)\n",
    "    plt.step(ccqe_true.energy, ccqe_true.xsec, where=\"mid\")\n",
    "    plt.step(ccqe_filtered.energy, ccqe_filtered.xsec, where=\"mid\")\n",
    "    axins.grid(True, \"both\")\n",
    "    inloc.mark_inset(ax, axins, loc1=loc[1], loc2=loc[2], fc=\"none\", ec=\"0.5\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "From now on, we use the flags (+f) for filtered data, (-s) for removing side effects."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<p> </p>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "_________________________________________\n",
    "## Interpolation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<p> </p>\n",
    "We'll keep the filtered way in the further analysis, without any other checks, since the reading technique used for the unfiltered data is not precise in itself."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In order to convolve interaction cross-section with the flux, one needs the same bining for the two histograms (the $\\texttt{numpy}$ function $\\texttt{convolve}$ takes two one-dimensionnal arrays). The way to do so is to interpolate the $(x,y)$ data of one of the two quantities with the $(x)$ of the other. Since :\n",
    "<ul>\n",
    "  <li>the flux is the \"input\" data of the FD (cross-section is more of a filter, a detector response);</li>\n",
    "  <li>the flux binning is smaller;</li>\n",
    "  <li>the flux data is \"cleaner\" (collected from T2K collab.) than the cross-section (read from a figure);</li>\n",
    "</ul> \n",
    "we choose to to interpolate the cross-section data to fit the flux binning."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "metadata": {
    "metadata": {}
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ccqe_interp = conv.xsecimport(\n",
    "    name=\"neutrino_ccqe.csv\",\n",
    "    mode=\"true filter interp\",\n",
    "    keep_left=5,\n",
    "    on=(t2kflux_2020_plus250kA_nominal_sk.minE + t2kflux_2020_plus250kA_nominal_sk.maxE)\n",
    "    / 2,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "metadata": {
    "metadata": {}
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x500 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.step(ccqe_filtered.energy, ccqe_filtered.xsec, label=r\"CCQE (+f-o)\", where=\"mid\")\n",
    "plt.step(\n",
    "    ccqe_interp.energy,\n",
    "    ccqe_interp.xsec,\n",
    "    label=r\"CCQE (+f-o+interpolated)\",\n",
    "    where=\"mid\",\n",
    ")\n",
    "plt.axvline(x=0.6, linestyle=\"--\", color=\"black\")\n",
    "plt.annotate(r\"600 MeV\", xy=(0.65, 2e-38), fontsize=10, rotation=90)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xscale(\"log\")\n",
    "# plt.yscale(\"log\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(r\"$E$ [GeV]\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(r\"$\\nu$ cross-section [$\\text{cm}^2$]\")\n",
    "# plt.ylim(bottom=1e-1)\n",
    "plt.title(r\"CCQE neutrino cross-section per nucleon\")\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We hereafter use the flag (+i) for interpolated data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "___________________________________________________________________"
   ]

    "## Multiplying flux and cross-section"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "metadata": {
    "metadata": {}
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "number = pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "for key in [\"minE\", \"maxE\"]:\n",
    "    number[key] = t2kflux_2020_plus250kA_nominal_sk[key]\n",
    "for key in [\"numu\", \"antinumu\", \"nue\", \"antinue\"]:\n",
    "    number[key] = (\n",
    "        ccqe_interp.xsec * t2kflux_2020_plus250kA_nominal_sk[key] / (50 * 1e21)\n",
    "    )"
   ]

    "# plt.ylim(bottom=1e-1)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]

    "number[\"total\"] = number.numu + number.nue + number.antinumu + number.antinue"

    "numu_total = ((number.maxE - number.minE) * 1e3 * number.numu).sum()\n",
    "numu_total"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<p> </p>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "_________________________\n",
    "## Ocillation probability"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "For a given bin of neutrino number density, for the sake of this study, we take as to compute the number density after oscillation, the mean energy of the bin. The correct way to do would be to have a Monte Carlo, taking a random value of energy inside the bin, with the probability given by the number density of the bin.\n",
    "\n",
    "The values taken to evaluate the expected number of events are those taken in the T2K 2021 analysis."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "metadata": {
    "metadata": {}
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "number_oscillated = pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "for key in [\"minE\", \"maxE\"]:\n",
    "    number_oscillated[key] = number[key]\n",
    "\n",
    "for key in [\"numu\", \"nue\", \"antinumu\", \"antinue\", \"nutau\", \"antinutau\"]:\n",
    "    number_oscillated[key] = 0.0\n",
    "\n",
    "number[\"nutau\"] = 0.0\n",
    "number[\"antinutau\"] = 0.0"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "metadata": {
    "metadata": {}
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "for i in range(len(number_oscillated)):\n",
    "    Pee, Pem, Pet, Pme, Pmm, Pmt, Pte, Ptm, Ptt = osc.probability_general(\n",
    "        E=(number_oscillated.maxE.loc[i] + number_oscillated.minE.loc[i]) / 2,\n",
    "        theta_12=np.arcsin(np.sqrt(0.304)),\n",
    "        theta_13=np.arcsin(np.sqrt(0.0212)),\n",
    "        theta_23=np.arcsin(np.sqrt(0.528)),\n",
    "        delta_cp=-1.601,\n",
    "        dm2_21=7.53e-5,\n",
    "        dm2_atm=2.509e-3,\n",
    "        compute_matrix_multiplication=True,\n",
    "        L=param.BASELINE * param.CONV_KM_TO_INV_EV,\n",
    "        ME=True,\n",
    "        MO=\"NO\",\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    number_oscillated.loc[i, \"numu\"] = (\n",
    "        number.loc[i, \"numu\"] * Pmm + number.loc[i, \"nue\"] * Pem\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    number_oscillated.loc[i, \"nue\"] = (\n",
    "        number.loc[i, \"nue\"] * Pee + number.loc[i, \"numu\"] * Pme\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    number_oscillated.loc[i, \"nutau\"] = (\n",
    "        number.loc[i, \"nue\"] * Pet + number.loc[i, \"numu\"] * Pmt\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    Pee, Pem, Pet, Pme, Pmm, Pmt, Pte, Ptm, Ptt = osc.probability_general_anti(\n",
    "        E=(number_oscillated.maxE.loc[i] + number_oscillated.minE.loc[i]) / 2,\n",
    "        theta_12=np.arcsin(np.sqrt(0.304)),\n",
    "        theta_13=np.arcsin(np.sqrt(0.0212)),\n",
    "        theta_23=np.arcsin(np.sqrt(0.528)),\n",
    "        delta_cp=-1.601,\n",
    "        dm2_21=7.53e-5,\n",
    "        dm2_atm=2.509e-3,\n",
    "        compute_matrix_multiplication=True,\n",
    "        L=param.BASELINE * param.CONV_KM_TO_INV_EV,\n",
    "        ME=True,\n",
    "        MO=\"NO\",\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    number_oscillated.loc[i, \"antinumu\"] = (\n",
    "        number.loc[i, \"antinumu\"] * Pmm + number.loc[i, \"antinue\"] * Pem\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    number_oscillated.loc[i, \"antinue\"] = (\n",
    "        number.loc[i, \"antinue\"] * Pee + number.loc[i, \"antinumu\"] * Pme\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    number_oscillated.loc[i, \"antinutau\"] = (\n",
    "        number.loc[i, \"antinue\"] * Pet + number.loc[i, \"antinumu\"] * Pmt\n",
    "    )"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 52,
   "metadata": {
    "metadata": {}
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1500x1000 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, axs = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(15, 10), sharex=\"col\", sharey=\"col\")\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in [0, 1]:\n",
    "    for key in [\"numu\", \"nue\", \"antinumu\", \"antinue\", \"nutau\", \"antinutau\"]:\n",
    "        axs[0, i].step(\n",
    "            number.minE,\n",
    "            number[key],\n",
    "            label=conv.print_dict[key],\n",
    "            color=colors[key],\n",
    "        )\n",
    "\n",
    "        axs[1, i].step(\n",
    "            number_oscillated.minE,\n",
    "            number_oscillated[key],\n",
    "            label=conv.print_dict[key] + r\" ($\\times \\mathcal{P}$)\",\n",
    "            color=colors[key],\n",
    "        )\n",
    "\n",
    "    axs[1, i].set_xlabel(r\"$E$ [GeV]\")\n",
    "\n",
    "for ax in axs.reshape(-1):\n",
    "    ax.set_xscale(\"log\")\n",
    "    ax.legend()\n",
    "    ax.text(\n",
    "        x=0.6,\n",
    "        y=0.5,\n",
    "        s=r\"600 MeV\",\n",
    "        ha=\"right\",\n",
    "        va=\"top\",\n",
    "        rotation=90,\n",
    "        transform=ax.get_xaxis_transform(),\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    ax.axvline(x=0.6, linestyle=\"--\", color=\"black\")\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(2):\n",
    "    axs[i, 0].set_yscale(\"log\")\n",
    "    # axs[i,0].set_ylim(bottom=1e-1)\n",
    "    axs[i, 1].yaxis.tick_right()\n",
    "\n",
    "axs[0, 0].set_ylabel(\n",
    "    r\"Number density [$\\text{MeV}^{-1} \\cdot \\text{PoT}^{-1} \\cdot \\text{nucleon}^{-1}$]\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "axs[1, 0].set_ylabel(\n",
    "    r\"Number density [$\\text{MeV}^{-1} \\cdot \\text{PoT}^{-1} \\cdot \\text{nucleon}^{-1}$]\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "fig.suptitle(\n",
    "    r\"[(T2K Flux 2020 | Nominal conditions | SK | $+250$ kA) $\\ \\times \\ $ (CCQE only)] $\\ \\ \\times \\ \\ $ (Oscillation probability | ME | NO)\",\n",
    "    fontsize=15,\n",
    ")\n",
    "fig.tight_layout()\n",
    "\n",
    "# plt.ylabel(r\"Detected $\\nu$ number density [$(\\text{MeV} \\cdot \\text{PoT})^{-1}$]\")\n",
    "# plt.ylim(bottom=1e-1)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 53,
   "metadata": {
    "metadata": {}
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "1.2444827386444819e-53"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 53,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "numu_total = (\n",
    "    (number_oscillated.maxE - number_oscillated.minE) * 1e3 * number_oscillated.numu\n",
    ").sum()\n",
    "numu_total"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<p> </p>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},

    "___________________________________"
   ]

       "<div>\n",
       "<style scoped>\n",
       "    .dataframe tbody tr th:only-of-type {\n",
       "        vertical-align: middle;\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    .dataframe tbody tr th {\n",
       "        vertical-align: top;\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    .dataframe thead th {\n",
       "        text-align: right;\n",

       "</style>\n",
       "<table border=\"1\" class=\"dataframe\">\n",

   "source": [
    "Before the convolution, let's normalize the curve so that its integral is 1."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 33,
   "metadata": {
    "metadata": {}
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "integral = 0\n",
    "for i in range(len(ccqe_energy_res_interp) - 1):\n",
    "    integral += ccqe_energy_res_interp.events.loc[i] * (\n",
    "        ccqe_energy_res_interp.relatenergy.loc[i + 1]\n",
    "        - ccqe_energy_res_interp.relatenergy.loc[i]\n",
    "    )\n",
    "ccqe_energy_res_interp.events = ccqe_energy_res_interp.events / integral"
   ]
  },

    "integral"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},

    "___________________________________________________"
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Convoluting the predicted number of neutrinos at SK with the energy resolution"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's focus on 1 bin of `number`, between `minE` and `maxE`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 36,
   "metadata": {
    "metadata": {}
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x500 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "n = 40\n",
    "plt.step(\n",
    "    number.minE.loc[n - 1 : n + 2],\n",
    "    number.numu.loc[n - 1 : n + 2],\n",
    "    where=\"pre\",\n",
    "    label=conv.print_dict[\"numu\"],\n",
    "    color=colors[\"numu\"],\n",
    ")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(r\"$E$ [GeV]\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\n",
    "    r\"Number density [$\\text{MeV}^{-1} \\cdot \\text{PoT}^{-1} \\cdot \\text{nucleon}^{-1}$]\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 37,
   "metadata": {
    "metadata": {}
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x500 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.step(\n",
    "    number.minE.loc[n - 1 : n + 2],\n",
    "    number.numu.loc[n - 1 : n + 2],\n",
    "    where=\"pre\",\n",
    "    label=conv.print_dict[\"numu\"],\n",
    "    color=colors[\"numu\"],\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "reds = [\"indianred\", \"red\", \"lightcoral\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in [n - 1, n, n + 1]:\n",
    "    Emoy = (number.minE.loc[i] + number.maxE.loc[i]) / 2\n",
    "\n",
    "    true_energy = ccqe_energy_res_interp.relatenergy * Emoy + Emoy\n",
    "    true_integral = number.numu.loc[i] * (number.maxE.loc[i] - number.minE.loc[i])\n",
    "\n",
    "    raw_integral = 0\n",
    "    for k in range(len(true_energy) - 1):\n",
    "        raw_integral += ccqe_energy_res_interp.events[k] * (\n",
    "            true_energy[k + 1] - true_energy[k]\n",
    "        )\n",
    "    true_events = ccqe_energy_res_interp.events * true_integral / raw_integral\n",
    "\n",
    "    interpolated = np.interp(\n",
    "        x=(number.maxE + number.minE) / 2, xp=true_energy, fp=true_events\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    interpolated_integral = (interpolated * (number.maxE - number.minE)).sum()\n",
    "    interpolated = interpolated * true_integral / interpolated_integral\n",
    "\n",
    "    plt.step(number.minE, interpolated, where=\"pre\", color=reds[i - n + 1])\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.yscale(\"log\")\n",
    "# plt.ylim(bottom=2e-56)\n",
    "plt.xlim(0, 1)\n",
    "plt.xlabel(r\"$E$ [GeV]\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\n",
    "    r\"Number density [$\\text{MeV}^{-1} \\cdot \\text{PoT}^{-1}\\cdot \\text{nucleon}^{-1}$]\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<p> </p>\n",
    "Then, doing so for each bin and summing every energy smearing :"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 38,
   "metadata": {
    "metadata": {}
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "smeared_number = pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "for key in [\"minE\", \"maxE\"]:\n",
    "    smeared_number[key] = number[key]\n",
    "\n",
    "for key in [\"numu\", \"nue\", \"antinumu\", \"antinue\"]:\n",
    "    smeared_number[key] = 0\n",
    "    for i in range(len(smeared_number)):\n",
    "        Emoy = (number.minE.loc[i] + number.maxE.loc[i]) / 2\n",
    "\n",
    "        true_energy = ccqe_energy_res_interp.relatenergy * Emoy + Emoy\n",
    "        true_integral = number[key].loc[i] * (number.maxE.loc[i] - number.minE.loc[i])\n",
    "\n",
    "        raw_integral = 0\n",
    "        for k in range(len(true_energy) - 1):\n",
    "            raw_integral += ccqe_energy_res_interp.events[k] * (\n",
    "                true_energy[k + 1] - true_energy[k]\n",
    "            )\n",
    "        true_events = ccqe_energy_res_interp.events * true_integral / raw_integral\n",
    "\n",
    "        interpolated = np.interp(\n",
    "            x=(number.maxE + number.minE) / 2, xp=true_energy, fp=true_events\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        interpolated_integral = (interpolated * (number.maxE - number.minE)).sum()\n",
    "        if interpolated_integral != 0:\n",
    "            interpolated = interpolated * true_integral / interpolated_integral\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            interpolated = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "        smeared_number[key] += interpolated"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 39,
   "metadata": {
    "metadata": {}
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",

     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"

   "source": [
    "plt.step(number.minE, number.numu, label=r\"$\\nu_\\mu$\")\n",
    "\n",

   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    ".. note:: Note that doing so, we get a side effect due to the wrong normalization of the smearing on the edges. Indeed, we stop the interpolation with the existing bining, then we normalize, without taking into accounts the energy lost in bins outside the initial bining. \n",
    "Here, the value at the edges being close to 0 for wide ranges, we do not search to correct this side effect."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 40,
   "metadata": {

   "cell_type": "code",

   "source": [
    "l1 = [x for x in range(10)]\n",
    "l2 = 10 * [0] + [5] * 5 + [0] * 5\n",
    "convf = np.convolve(l2, l1, mode=\"full\")\n",
    "convs = np.convolve(l1, l2, mode=\"same\")\n",
    "convv = np.convolve(l1, l2, mode=\"valid\")\n",
    "plt.plot(l1, linestyle=\"dashed\")\n",
    "plt.plot(l2, linestyle=\"dashed\")\n",
    "for l in [convf, convs, convv]:\n",
    "    plt.plot(l)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 42,
   "metadata": {
    "metadata": {}
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Sum of uniform pmf: 0.9999999999998996\n",
      "Sum of normal pmf: 1.0000000000023075\n",
      "Sum of convoluted pmf: 1.0000000000023057\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x500 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import scipy.stats as stats\n",
    "from scipy import signal\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "uniform_dist = stats.uniform(loc=2, scale=3)\n",
    "std = 0.25\n",
    "normal_dist = stats.norm(loc=0, scale=std)\n",
    "\n",
    "delta = 1e-4\n",
    "big_grid = np.arange(-10, 10, delta)\n",
    "\n",
    "pmf1 = uniform_dist.pdf(big_grid) * delta\n",
    "print(\"Sum of uniform pmf: \" + str(sum(pmf1)))\n",
    "\n",
    "pmf2 = normal_dist.pdf(big_grid) * delta\n",
    "print(\"Sum of normal pmf: \" + str(sum(pmf2)))\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "conv_pmf = signal.fftconvolve(pmf2, pmf1, \"same\")\n",
    "print(\"Sum of convoluted pmf: \" + str(sum(conv_pmf)))\n",
    "\n",
    "pdf1 = pmf1 / delta\n",
    "pdf2 = pmf2 / delta\n",
    "conv_pdf = conv_pmf / delta\n",
    "# print(\"Integration of convoluted pdf: \" + str(np.trapz(conv_pdf, big_grid)))\n",
    "\n",
    "# new_grid=np.arange(0,len(conv_pdf),delta)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(big_grid, pdf1, label=\"Uniform\")\n",
    "plt.plot(big_grid, pdf2, label=\"Gaussian\")\n",
    "plt.plot(big_grid, pdf1 * pdf2, label=\"product\")\n",
    "plt.plot(big_grid, conv_pdf, label=\"Sum\")\n",
    "plt.legend(loc=\"best\"), plt.suptitle(\"PDFs\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 43,
   "metadata": {
    "metadata": {}
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    ".. warning::\n",
    "    The following is not working anymore, due to a mistake in the renormalization of the cross-section. Please skip directly to the next subsection."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The data is not very smooth, since it has been read-out from a figure in an article. The shape of $\\sigma / E$ looks like a Maxwell-Boltzmann, so we can try fitting it."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 45,
   "metadata": {
    "metadata": {}
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def maxwell(x, a, b):\n",
    "    return np.sqrt(2 / np.pi) * ((x) ** 2 / a**3) * np.exp(-((x + b) ** 2) / (2 * a**2))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 46,
   "metadata": {
    "metadata": {}
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def lognormal(x, sigma, mu):\n",
    "    return (1 / (x * sigma * np.sqrt(2 * np.pi))) * np.exp(\n",
    "        -((np.log(x) - mu) ** 2) / (2 * sigma**2)\n",
    "    )"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 47,
   "metadata": {
    "metadata": {}
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# params = stats.maxwell.fit(xsec.xsec, floc=0)\n",
    "parameters, covariance = optimize.curve_fit(lognormal, ccqe.energy, ccqe.xsec)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 48,
   "metadata": {
    "metadata": {}
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {

   "source": [
    "plt.step(ccqe.energy, ccqe.xsec, label=r\"CCQE\", where=\"mid\")\n",
    "plt.plot(ccqe.energy, lognormal(ccqe.energy, *parameters))\n",
    "plt.axvline(x=0.6, linestyle=\"--\", color=\"black\")\n",
    "plt.annotate(r\"600 MeV\", xy=(0.45, 2e-1), fontsize=10, rotation=90)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xscale(\"log\")\n",
    "# plt.yscale(\"log\")\n",
